☁️ AWS Services Used & Why
🖥️ Compute Layer
Amazon EC2
Hosts microservices
Provides scalable virtual machines
Amazon EKS
Container orchestration
Auto-scaling and high availability
🌐 Networking & API Management
Amazon API Gateway
Entry point for all client requests
Handles routing, throttling, and security
Elastic Load Balancing
Distributes traffic across services
Improves availability
🗄️ Database Layer
Amazon RDS
Managed MySQL/PostgreSQL database
Automated backups and scaling
Amazon DynamoDB
High-performance NoSQL database
Suitable for transaction logs
⚡ Caching
Amazon ElastiCache
Uses Redis
Reduces database load and improves response time
🔐 Security
AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM)
Manages permissions and roles
Amazon Cognito
User authentication and authorization
📦 Storage
Amazon S3
Stores documents, logs, and backups
📊 Monitoring & Logging
Amazon CloudWatch
Tracks metrics and logs
Alerts on failures
